File: e2e/strict-csp.e2e.ts. Three fixtureTest blocks create tmpDir via fs.mkdtempSync but place the fs.rmSync cleanup at the END of the test body (lines ~643, ~702, ~795) WITHOUT a try/finally. If any assertion or await before the cleanup line throws, tmpDir leaks.

Fix: For each affected test, wrap the body after tmpDir creation in try/finally:
```
const tmpDir = fs.mkdtempSync(...);
try {
  // ... test body ...
} finally {
  fs.rmSync(tmpDir, { recursive: true, force: true });
}
```
The page.close() call can remain inside the try block since the fixture handles context cleanup.

File: e2e/analyze-site.e2e.ts, lines 104-125. The shared server is started in beforeAll (line 107-109) and used via `analyzeSiteServer?.url ?? ''` (line 125 and 11 other locations). If beforeAll fails, analyzeSiteServer stays undefined, and all 12 tests silently construct URLs like '/cookie-session/' (just the path) which produce misleading tool errors.

Fix: Add a guard function that throws a clear error:
```typescript
const getServerUrl = (): string => {
  if (!analyzeSiteServer) {
    throw new Error('Analyze-site test server not started — check beforeAll for errors');
  }
  return analyzeSiteServer.url;
};
```
Then replace all `analyzeSiteServer?.url ?? ''` with `getServerUrl()`. This gives immediate, clear errors instead of 12 cascading tool failures.
